      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TULSA (5) is overdue for a maiden success having placed at two of eight starts, the latest missing the frame when sixth at Ballarat. Although yet to win tends to go well here. Has ability and looks hard to stop. BLAME WALLY (1) shows ability but remains a maiden after 39 starts. Is better than last start when out of the placings, finishing seventh (29.13) at Bendigo. Key runner on best form. MAJOR ENVY (4) turned in a better effort at Ballarat last start, finishing third behind Lochinvar Dude (26.03) in a Maiden. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Bold showing expected. PAW JEANIE (2) is a Mark Delbridge-trained newcomer by Jarick Bale out of Gracie Bale. Drawn well and should get her chance. Profiles nicely but market best guide to ability.",
